BDD is for Acceptance testing
BDD is basically development process

Actual BDD- is for understanding the requirements
Modified form of BDD - Writing Acceptance testing (ATDD-Acceptance Test Driven Development)

1.create maven project
2.Add Dependencies
    1.cucumber-java
    2.cucumber-testng
    3.selenium
3.Architecture of cucumber
    1.Feature file (.feature) Gherkin code
    2.Step definition (.java)
    to connect the feature file and step definition we connect with RunnerTest

    Feature file
        In order to {business goal}
        As a {role}
        I would like to {Visible change in the application}
    Scenario
        1.provide scenario title
        2.Add minimum one given, when, then
            given-prerequisite
            when-actions
            then-verifications



